annotationA: Ubiquitin-60S ribosomal protein L40; Ubiquitin: exists either covalently attached to another protein, or free (unanchored). When covalently bound, it is conjugated to target proteins via an isopeptide bond either as a monomer (monoubiquitin), a polymer linked via different Lys residues of the ubiquitin (polyubiquitin chains) or a linear polymer linked via the initiator Met of the ubiquitin (linear polyubiquitin chains). annotationB: Ribosomal protein S3A is an essential component of the small ribosomal subunit that functions in protein synthesis. It is classified as a 'Minute' gene as heterozygous mutants exhibit a slower developmental rate and small adult bristles
